Initialize a new HBaseKijiResult.

Parameters:
entityId - EntityId of the row from which to read cells.
dataRequest - KijiDataRequest defining the values to retrieve.
unPagedResult - Result containing all non-paged values requested by dataRequest. Includes values which should be removed during post-processing such as the first value from a paged column, or extra versions of a column with a lower max versions than the highest in the request.
columnNameTranslator - ColumnNameTranslator to use for decoding KeyValues.
cellDecoderProvider - Provider for cell decoders to use for decoding KeyValues.
table - Kiji table from which to retrieve cells.

iterator

public <T> Iterator<KijiCell<T>> iterator(KijiColumnName column)
Get an iterator of the cells in the given qualified column or map-type family.

The column may not be a group-type family. The column may be marked as paged or unpaged in the data request which defines this KijiResult.

Multiple calls to iterator(column) with the same column will return separate iterators. If the column is paged, data will be re-requested from the underlying store and two active iterators on a paged column will hold two pages in memory simultaneously.

If the given column is a map-type family qualifiers are sorted lexicographically. Within one qualified column, cells are sorted most recent first.

Specified by:
iterator in interface KijiResult
Type Parameters:
T - type of the value in the given column.
Parameters:
column - qualified column or map-type family from which to get an iterator of cells.
Returns:
an iterator of the cells in the given qualified column or map-type family.

iterator

public Iterator<KijiCell<?>> iterator()

Multiple calls to iterator() will return separate iterators. If the column data request which defines this KijiResult contains paged columns, those pages will be re-requested from the underlying store. Two active iterators may hold two pages of data in memory simultaneously.

The order of columns in the iterator is not defined, but all non-paged columns will appear before all paged columns. Within one qualified column, cells are sorted most recent first.

Specified by:
iterator in interface Iterable<KijiCell<?>>
Specified by:
iterator in interface KijiResult
Returns:
a new Iterator over all the cells in this KijiResult.
